##
## Ends in an error in state: 183.
##
## specifier_qualifier_list(type_name) -> option(type_qualifier_list) TYPEDEF_NAME option(type_qualifier_list) . [ STAR RPAREN LPAREN LBRACK ]
## type_qualifier_list -> option(type_qualifier_list) . type_qualifier [ VOLATILE STAR RPAREN RESTRICT PACKED LPAREN LBRACK CONST ATTRIBUTE ALIGNAS ]
##

# We are trying to recognize a specifier_qualifier_list.
# This is in the context of a type_name.
# Thus, this specifier_qualifier_list should be followed with
# abstract_declarator? RPAREN.
# Thus, we expect either:
# 1. One more type qualifier (part of the type name)
# 2. An abstract declarator  (part of the type name)
# 3. A closing parenthesis   (which follows the type name).
#
# What we have read so far in fact forms a valid type name. If we could
# (spuriously) reduce the first production above, we would find that we
# have a complete specifier_qualifier_list(type_name), hence a complete
# type name.

Up to this point, a type name has been recognized.
At this point, one of the following is expected:
  a type qualifier,          continuing this type name; or
  an abstract declarator,    continuing this type name; or
  a closing parenthesis ')', following this type name.

