## In state 215, spurious reduction of production option(specifier_qualifier_list_no_typedef_name) -> 
## In state 327, spurious reduction of production specifier_qualifier_list_no_typedef_name -> type_specifier_no_typedef_name option(specifier_qualifier_list_no_typedef_name) 
## In state 320, spurious reduction of production option(specifier_qualifier_list_no_typedef_name) -> specifier_qualifier_list_no_typedef_name 
## In state 328, spurious reduction of production specifier_qualifier_list(type_name) -> option(type_qualifier_list) type_specifier_no_typedef_name option(specifier_qualifier_list_no_typedef_name) 
##

# This situation is rather similar to the one above.
# We are also trying to recognize a type name.
# As above, the continuation is abstract_declarator? RPAREN.
# Furthermore, the list of specifiers and qualifiers could
# be incomplete (this state is reached via a spurious reduction).
# Thus, we expect either:
# 1. One more type qualifier
# 2. One more type specifier (which cannot be a typedef name)
# 3. An abstract declarator
# 4. A closing parenthesis.

Up to this point, a type name has been recognized.
At this point, one of the following is expected:
  a type qualifier,          continuing this type name; or
  a type specifier,          continuing this type name; or
  an abstract declarator,    continuing this type name; or
  a closing parenthesis ')', following this type name.

